106#define WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(channel, fmt, ...) RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(channel, "%p - [PID=%i] WebProcessProxy::" fmt, this, processIdentifier(), ##__VA_ARGS__)

111static bool isMainThreadOrCheckDisabled()
112{
113#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
114 return LIKELY(RunLoop::isMain()) || !linkedOnOrAfter(WebCore::SDKVersion::FirstWithMainThreadReleaseAssertionInWebPageProxy);
115#elif PLATFORM(MAC)
116 return LIKELY(RunLoop::isMain()) || !linkedOnOrAfter(WebCore::SDKVersion::FirstWithMainThreadReleaseAssertionInWebPageProxy);
117#else
118 return RunLoop::isMain();
119#endif
120}
121
122HashMap<ProcessIdentifier, WebProcessProxy*>& WebProcessProxy::allProcesses()
123{
124 ASSERT(isMainThreadOrCheckDisabled());
125 static NeverDestroyed<HashMap<ProcessIdentifier, WebProcessProxy*>> map;
126 return map;
127}
128
129WebProcessProxy* WebProcessProxy::processForIdentifier(ProcessIdentifier identifier)
130{
131 return allProcesses().get(identifier);
132}
133
134static WebProcessProxy::WebPageProxyMap& globalPageMap()
135{
136 ASSERT(isMainThreadOrCheckDisabled());
137 static NeverDestroyed<WebProcessProxy::WebPageProxyMap> pageMap;
138 return pageMap;
139}
140
141void WebProcessProxy::forWebPagesWithOrigin(PAL::SessionID sessionID, const SecurityOriginData& origin, const Function<void(WebPageProxy&)>& callback)
142{
143 for (auto* page : globalPageMap().values()) {
144 if (page->sessionID() != sessionID || SecurityOriginData::fromURL(URL { { }, page->currentURL() }) != origin)
145 continue;
146 callback(*page);
147 }
148}

150Ref<WebProcessProxy> WebProcessProxy::create(WebProcessPool& processPool, WebsiteDataStore* websiteDataStore, IsPrewarmed isPrewarmed, ShouldLaunchProcess shouldLaunchProcess)
151{
152 auto proxy = adoptRef(*new WebProcessProxy(processPool, websiteDataStore, isPrewarmed));
153 if (shouldLaunchProcess == ShouldLaunchProcess::Yes)
154 proxy->connect();
155 return proxy;
156}
157
158#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
159Ref<WebProcessProxy> WebProcessProxy::createForServiceWorkers(WebProcessPool& processPool, RegistrableDomain&& registrableDomain, WebsiteDataStore& websiteDataStore)
160{
161 auto proxy = adoptRef(*new WebProcessProxy(processPool, &websiteDataStore, IsPrewarmed::No));
162 proxy->m_registrableDomain = WTFMove(registrableDomain);
163 proxy->enableServiceWorkers(processPool.userContentControllerIdentifierForServiceWorkers());
164 proxy->connect();
165 return proxy;
166}
167#endif

169#if PLATFORM(COCOA) && ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
170class UIProxyForCapture final : public UserMediaCaptureManagerProxy::ConnectionProxy {
171 WTF_MAKE_FAST_ALLOCATED;
172public:
173 explicit UIProxyForCapture(WebProcessProxy& process) : m_process(process) { }
174private:
175 void addMessageReceiver(IPC::ReceiverName messageReceiverName, IPC::MessageReceiver& receiver) final { m_process.addMessageReceiver(messageReceiverName, receiver); }
176 void removeMessageReceiver(IPC::ReceiverName messageReceiverName) final { m_process.removeMessageReceiver(messageReceiverName); }
177 IPC::Connection& connection() final { return *m_process.connection(); }
178 Logger& logger() final
179 {
180 if (!m_logger) {
181 m_logger = Logger::create(this);
182 m_logger->setEnabled(this, m_process.sessionID().isAlwaysOnLoggingAllowed());
183 }
184 return *m_logger;
185 }
186 bool willStartCapture(CaptureDevice::DeviceType) const final
187 {
188 // FIXME: We should validate this is granted.
189 return true;
190 }
191
192 RefPtr<Logger> m_logger;
193 WebProcessProxy& m_process;
194};

196
197WebProcessProxy::WebProcessProxy(WebProcessPool& processPool, WebsiteDataStore* websiteDataStore, IsPrewarmed isPrewarmed)
198 : AuxiliaryProcessProxy(processPool.alwaysRunsAtBackgroundPriority())
199 , m_backgroundResponsivenessTimer(*this)
200 , m_processPool(processPool, isPrewarmed == IsPrewarmed::Yes ? IsWeak::Yes : IsWeak::No)
201 , m_mayHaveUniversalFileReadSandboxExtension(false)
202 , m_numberOfTimesSuddenTerminationWasDisabled(0)
203 , m_throttler(*this, processPool.shouldTakeUIBackgroundAssertion())
204#if ENABLE(ROUTING_ARBITRATION)
205 , m_routingArbitrator(makeUniqueRef<AudioSessionRoutingArbitratorProxy>(*this))
206#endif
207 , m_isResponsive(NoOrMaybe::Maybe)
208 , m_visiblePageCounter([this](RefCounterEvent) { updateBackgroundResponsivenessTimer(); })
209 , m_websiteDataStore(websiteDataStore)
210#if PLATFORM(COCOA) && ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
211 , m_userMediaCaptureManagerProxy(makeUnique<UserMediaCaptureManagerProxy>(makeUniqueRef<UIProxyForCapture>(*this)))
212#endif
213 , m_isPrewarmed(isPrewarmed == IsPrewarmed::Yes)
214 , m_shutdownPreventingScopeCounter([this](RefCounterEvent event) { if (event == RefCounterEvent::Decrement) maybeShutDown(); })
215{
216 RELEASE_ASSERT(isMainThreadOrCheckDisabled());
217 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(Process, "constructor:");
218
219 auto result = allProcesses().add(coreProcessIdentifier(), this);
220 ASSERT_UNUSED(result, result.isNewEntry);
221
222 WebPasteboardProxy::singleton().addWebProcessProxy(*this);
223
224 platformInitialize();
225}

229{
230}
231#endif
232
233WebProcessProxy::~WebProcessProxy()
234{
235 RELEASE_ASSERT(isMainThreadOrCheckDisabled());
236 ASSERT(m_pageURLRetainCountMap.isEmpty());
237 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(Process, "destructor:");
238
239 for (auto identifier : m_speechRecognitionServerMap.keys())
240 removeMessageReceiver(Messages::SpeechRecognitionServer::messageReceiverName(), identifier);
241
242#if ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
243 if (m_speechRecognitionRemoteRealtimeMediaSourceManager)
244 removeMessageReceiver(Messages::SpeechRecognitionRemoteRealtimeMediaSourceManager::messageReceiverName());
245#endif
246
247 auto result = allProcesses().remove(coreProcessIdentifier());
248 ASSERT_UNUSED(result, result);
249
250 WebPasteboardProxy::singleton().removeWebProcessProxy(*this);
251
252#if HAVE(CVDISPLAYLINK)
253 if (state() == State::Running)
254 processPool().stopDisplayLinks(*connection());
255#endif
256
257 auto isResponsiveCallbacks = WTFMove(m_isResponsiveCallbacks);
258 for (auto& callback : isResponsiveCallbacks)
259 callback(false);
260
261 if (m_webConnection)
262 m_webConnection->invalidate();
263
264 while (m_numberOfTimesSuddenTerminationWasDisabled-- > 0)
265 WebCore::enableSuddenTermination();
266
267#if PLATFORM(MAC)
268 HighPerformanceGPUManager::singleton().removeProcessRequiringHighPerformance(*this);
269#endif
270
271 platformDestroy();
272}

274#if !PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
275void WebProcessProxy::platformDestroy()
276{
277}
278#endif

280void WebProcessProxy::setIsInProcessCache(bool value)
281{
282 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(Process, "setIsInProcessCache(%d)", value);
283 if (value) {
284 RELEASE_ASSERT(m_pageMap.isEmpty());
285 RELEASE_ASSERT(!m_suspendedPageCount);
286 RELEASE_ASSERT(m_provisionalPages.isEmpty());
287 }
288
289 ASSERT(m_isInProcessCache != value);
290 m_isInProcessCache = value;
291
292 if (!m_isInProcessCache)
293 platformResumeProcess();
294
295 sendWithAsyncReply(Messages::WebProcess::SetIsInProcessCache(m_isInProcessCache), [weakThis = makeWeakPtr(*this), isEnteringProcessCache = value]() mutable {
296 if (isEnteringProcessCache && weakThis && weakThis->m_isInProcessCache)
297 weakThis->platformSuspendProcess();
298 });
299
300 if (m_isInProcessCache) {
301 // WebProcessProxy objects normally keep the process pool alive but we do not want this to be the case
302 // for cached processes or it would leak the pool.
303 m_processPool.setIsWeak(IsWeak::Yes);
304 } else {
305 RELEASE_ASSERT(m_processPool);
306 m_processPool.setIsWeak(IsWeak::No);
307 }
308}
309
310void WebProcessProxy::setWebsiteDataStore(WebsiteDataStore& dataStore)
311{
312 ASSERT(!m_websiteDataStore);
313 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(Process, "setWebsiteDataStore() dataStore=%p, sessionID=%" PRIu64, &dataStore, dataStore.sessionID().toUInt64());
314 m_websiteDataStore = &dataStore;
315#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
316 dataStore.sendNetworkProcessXPCEndpointToWebProcess(*this);
317#endif
318 updateRegistrationWithDataStore();
319 send(Messages::WebProcess::SetWebsiteDataStoreParameters(processPool().webProcessDataStoreParameters(*this, dataStore)), 0);
320}
321
322bool WebProcessProxy::isDummyProcessProxy() const
323{
324 return m_websiteDataStore && processPool().dummyProcessProxy(m_websiteDataStore->sessionID()) == this;
325}
326
327void WebProcessProxy::updateRegistrationWithDataStore()
328{
329 if (!m_websiteDataStore)
330 return;
331
332 bool shouldBeRegistered = pageCount() || provisionalPageCount();
333 if (shouldBeRegistered)
334 m_websiteDataStore->registerProcess(*this);
335 else
336 m_websiteDataStore->unregisterProcess(*this);
337}

339void WebProcessProxy::addProvisionalPageProxy(ProvisionalPageProxy& provisionalPage)
340{
341 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(Loading, "addProvisionalPageProxy: provisionalPage=%p, pageProxyID=%" PRIu64 ", webPageID=%" PRIu64, &provisionalPage, provisionalPage.page().identifier().toUInt64(), provisionalPage.webPageID().toUInt64());
342
343 ASSERT(!m_isInProcessCache);
344 ASSERT(!m_provisionalPages.contains(&provisionalPage));
345 m_provisionalPages.add(&provisionalPage);
346 updateRegistrationWithDataStore();
347}
348
349void WebProcessProxy::removeProvisionalPageProxy(ProvisionalPageProxy& provisionalPage)
350{
351 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(Loading, "removeProvisionalPageProxy: provisionalPage=%p, pageProxyID=%" PRIu64 ", webPageID=%" PRIu64, &provisionalPage, provisionalPage.page().identifier().toUInt64(), provisionalPage.webPageID().toUInt64());
352
353 ASSERT(m_provisionalPages.contains(&provisionalPage));
354 m_provisionalPages.remove(&provisionalPage);
355 updateRegistrationWithDataStore();
356 if (m_provisionalPages.isEmpty())
357 maybeShutDown();
358}

360void WebProcessProxy::getLaunchOptions(ProcessLauncher::LaunchOptions& launchOptions)
361{
362 launchOptions.processType = ProcessLauncher::ProcessType::Web;
363
364 AuxiliaryProcessProxy::getLaunchOptions(launchOptions);
365
366 if (!m_processPool->customWebContentServiceBundleIdentifier().isEmpty())
367 launchOptions.customWebContentServiceBundleIdentifier = m_processPool->customWebContentServiceBundleIdentifier().ascii();
368 if (WebKit::isInspectorProcessPool(processPool()))
369 launchOptions.extraInitializationData.add("inspector-process"_s, "1"_s);
370
371 auto overrideLanguages = m_processPool->configuration().overrideLanguages();
372 if (overrideLanguages.isEmpty())
373 overrideLanguages = platformOverrideLanguages();
374 if (!overrideLanguages.isEmpty()) {
375 StringBuilder languageString;
376 for (size_t i = 0; i < overrideLanguages.size(); ++i) {
377 if (i)
378 languageString.append(',');
379 languageString.append(overrideLanguages[i]);
380 }
381 launchOptions.extraInitializationData.add("OverrideLanguages"_s, languageString.toString());
382 }
383
384 launchOptions.nonValidInjectedCodeAllowed = shouldAllowNonValidInjectedCode();
385
386 if (isPrewarmed())
387 launchOptions.extraInitializationData.add("is-prewarmed"_s, "1"_s);
388
389#if PLATFORM(PLAYSTATION)
390 launchOptions.processPath = m_processPool->webProcessPath();
391 launchOptions.userId = m_processPool->userId();
392#endif
393
394 if (processPool().shouldMakeNextWebProcessLaunchFailForTesting()) {
395 processPool().setShouldMakeNextWebProcessLaunchFailForTesting(false);
396 launchOptions.shouldMakeProcessLaunchFailForTesting = true;
397 }
398
399 if (m_serviceWorkerInformation) {
400 launchOptions.extraInitializationData.add("service-worker-process"_s, "1"_s);
401 launchOptions.extraInitializationData.add("registrable-domain"_s, m_registrableDomain->string());
402 }
403}

411bool WebProcessProxy::shouldSendPendingMessage(const PendingMessage& message)
412{
413 if (message.encoder->messageName() == IPC::MessageName::WebPage_LoadRequestWaitingForProcessLaunch) {
414 auto buffer = message.encoder->buffer();
415 auto bufferSize = message.encoder->bufferSize();
416 auto decoder = IPC::Decoder::create(buffer, bufferSize, nullptr, { });
417 ASSERT(decoder);
418 if (!decoder)
419 return false;
420
421 LoadParameters loadParameters;
422 URL resourceDirectoryURL;
423 WebPageProxyIdentifier pageID;
424 bool checkAssumedReadAccessToResourceURL;
425 if (decoder->decode(loadParameters) && decoder->decode(resourceDirectoryURL) && decoder->decode(pageID) && decoder->decode(checkAssumedReadAccessToResourceURL)) {
426 if (auto* page = WebProcessProxy::webPage(pageID)) {
427 page->maybeInitializeSandboxExtensionHandle(static_cast<WebProcessProxy&>(*this), loadParameters.request.url(), resourceDirectoryURL, loadParameters.sandboxExtensionHandle, checkAssumedReadAccessToResourceURL);
428 send(Messages::WebPage::LoadRequest(loadParameters), decoder->destinationID());
429 }
430 } else
431 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
432 return false;
433 }
434 return true;
435}
436
437void WebProcessProxy::connectionWillOpen(IPC::Connection& connection)
438{
439 ASSERT(this->connection() == &connection);
440
441 // Throttling IPC messages coming from the WebProcesses so that the UIProcess stays responsive, even
442 // if one of the WebProcesses misbehaves.
443 connection.enableIncomingMessagesThrottling();
444
445 // Use this flag to force synchronous messages to be treated as asynchronous messages in the WebProcess.
446 // Otherwise, the WebProcess would process incoming synchronous IPC while waiting for a synchronous IPC
447 // reply from the UIProcess, which would be unsafe.
448 connection.setOnlySendMessagesAsDispatchWhenWaitingForSyncReplyWhenProcessingSuchAMessage(true);
449
450#if ENABLE(SEC_ITEM_SHIM)
451 SecItemShimProxy::singleton().initializeConnection(connection);
452#endif
453}
454
455void WebProcessProxy::processWillShutDown(IPC::Connection& connection)
456{
457 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(Process, "processWillShutDown:");
458 ASSERT_UNUSED(connection, this->connection() == &connection);
459
460#if HAVE(CVDISPLAYLINK)
461 processPool().stopDisplayLinks(connection);
462#endif
463}
464
465void WebProcessProxy::shutDown()
466{
467 RELEASE_ASSERT(isMainThreadOrCheckDisabled());
468 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(Process, "shutDown:");
469
470 if (m_isInProcessCache) {
471 processPool().webProcessCache().removeProcess(*this, WebProcessCache::ShouldShutDownProcess::No);
472 ASSERT(!m_isInProcessCache);
473 }
474
475 shutDownProcess();
476
477 if (m_webConnection) {
478 m_webConnection->invalidate();
479 m_webConnection = nullptr;
480 }
481
482 m_backgroundResponsivenessTimer.invalidate();
483 m_activityForHoldingLockedFiles = nullptr;
484 m_audibleMediaActivity = std::nullopt;
485
486 for (auto& frame : copyToVector(m_frameMap.values()))
487 frame->webProcessWillShutDown();
488 m_frameMap.clear();
489
490 for (auto* webUserContentControllerProxy : m_webUserContentControllerProxies)
491 webUserContentControllerProxy->removeProcess(*this);
492 m_webUserContentControllerProxies.clear();
493
494 m_userInitiatedActionMap.clear();
495 m_sleepDisablers.clear();
496
497#if ENABLE(ROUTING_ARBITRATION)
498 m_routingArbitrator->processDidTerminate();
499#endif
500
501#if ENABLE(ATTACHMENT_ELEMENT)
502 m_hasIssuedAttachmentElementRelatedSandboxExtensions = false;
503#endif
504
505 m_processPool->disconnectProcess(*this);
506}

538Ref<WebPageProxy> WebProcessProxy::createWebPage(PageClient& pageClient, Ref<API::PageConfiguration>&& pageConfiguration)
539{
540 Ref<WebPageProxy> webPage = WebPageProxy::create(pageClient, *this, WTFMove(pageConfiguration));
541
542 addExistingWebPage(webPage.get(), BeginsUsingDataStore::Yes);
543
544 return webPage;
545}
546
547void WebProcessProxy::addExistingWebPage(WebPageProxy& webPage, BeginsUsingDataStore beginsUsingDataStore)
548{
549 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(Process, "addExistingWebPage: webPage=%p, pageProxyID=%" PRIu64 ", webPageID=%" PRIu64, &webPage, webPage.identifier().toUInt64(), webPage.webPageID().toUInt64());
550
551 ASSERT(!m_pageMap.contains(webPage.identifier()));
552 ASSERT(!globalPageMap().contains(webPage.identifier()));
553 RELEASE_ASSERT(!m_isInProcessCache);
554 ASSERT(!m_websiteDataStore || m_websiteDataStore == &webPage.websiteDataStore());
555
556 if (beginsUsingDataStore == BeginsUsingDataStore::Yes) {
557 RELEASE_ASSERT(m_processPool);
558 m_processPool->pageBeginUsingWebsiteDataStore(webPage.identifier(), webPage.websiteDataStore());
559 }
560
561 m_pageMap.set(webPage.identifier(), &webPage);
562 globalPageMap().set(webPage.identifier(), &webPage);
563
564 updateRegistrationWithDataStore();
565 updateBackgroundResponsivenessTimer();
566}
567
568void WebProcessProxy::markIsNoLongerInPrewarmedPool()
569{
570 ASSERT(m_isPrewarmed);
571 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(Process, "markIsNoLongerInPrewarmedPool:");
572
573 m_isPrewarmed = false;
574 RELEASE_ASSERT(m_processPool);
575 m_processPool.setIsWeak(IsWeak::No);
576
577 send(Messages::WebProcess::MarkIsNoLongerPrewarmed(), 0);
578}
579
580void WebProcessProxy::removeWebPage(WebPageProxy& webPage, EndsUsingDataStore endsUsingDataStore)
581{
582 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(Process, "removeWebPage: webPage=%p, pageProxyID=%" PRIu64 ", webPageID=%" PRIu64, &webPage, webPage.identifier().toUInt64(), webPage.webPageID().toUInt64());
583 auto* removedPage = m_pageMap.take(webPage.identifier());
584 ASSERT_UNUSED(removedPage, removedPage == &webPage);
585 removedPage = globalPageMap().take(webPage.identifier());
586 ASSERT_UNUSED(removedPage, removedPage == &webPage);
587
588 if (endsUsingDataStore == EndsUsingDataStore::Yes)
589 m_processPool->pageEndUsingWebsiteDataStore(webPage.identifier(), webPage.websiteDataStore());
590
591 removeVisitedLinkStoreUser(webPage.visitedLinkStore(), webPage.identifier());
592 updateRegistrationWithDataStore();
593 updateAudibleMediaAssertions();
594 updateBackgroundResponsivenessTimer();
595
596 maybeShutDown();
597}
598
599void WebProcessProxy::addVisitedLinkStoreUser(VisitedLinkStore& visitedLinkStore, WebPageProxyIdentifier pageID)
600{
601 auto& users = m_visitedLinkStoresWithUsers.ensure(&visitedLinkStore, [] {
602 return HashSet<WebPageProxyIdentifier> { };
603 }).iterator->value;
604
605 ASSERT(!users.contains(pageID));
606 users.add(pageID);
607
608 if (users.size() == 1)
609 visitedLinkStore.addProcess(*this);
610}
611
612void WebProcessProxy::removeVisitedLinkStoreUser(VisitedLinkStore& visitedLinkStore, WebPageProxyIdentifier pageID)
613{
614 auto it = m_visitedLinkStoresWithUsers.find(&visitedLinkStore);
615 if (it == m_visitedLinkStoresWithUsers.end())
616 return;
617
618 auto& users = it->value;
619 users.remove(pageID);
620 if (users.isEmpty()) {
621 m_visitedLinkStoresWithUsers.remove(it);
622 visitedLinkStore.removeProcess(*this);
623 }
624}

626void WebProcessProxy::addWebUserContentControllerProxy(WebUserContentControllerProxy& proxy)

628 m_webUserContentControllerProxies.add(&proxy);
629 proxy.addProcess(*this);
630}

635 m_webUserContentControllerProxies.remove(&proxy);

637
638void WebProcessProxy::assumeReadAccessToBaseURL(WebPageProxy& page, const String& urlString)
639{
640 URL url(URL(), urlString);
641 if (!url.isLocalFile())
642 return;
643
644 // There's a chance that urlString does not point to a directory.
645 // Get url's base URL to add to m_localPathsWithAssumedReadAccess.
646 auto path = url.truncatedForUseAsBase().fileSystemPath();
647 if (path.isNull())
648 return;
649
650 // Client loads an alternate string. This doesn't grant universal file read, but the web process is assumed
651 // to have read access to this directory already.
652 m_localPathsWithAssumedReadAccess.add(path);
653 page.addPreviouslyVisitedPath(path);
654}
655
656bool WebProcessProxy::hasAssumedReadAccessToURL(const URL& url) const
657{
658 if (!url.isLocalFile())
659 return false;
660
661 String path = url.fileSystemPath();
662 auto startsWithURLPath = [&path](const String& assumedAccessPath) {
663 // There are no ".." components, because URL removes those.
664 return path.startsWith(assumedAccessPath);
665 };
666
667 auto& platformPaths = platformPathsWithAssumedReadAccess();
668 auto platformPathsEnd = platformPaths.end();
669 if (std::find_if(platformPaths.begin(), platformPathsEnd, startsWithURLPath) != platformPathsEnd)
670 return true;
671
672 auto localPathsEnd = m_localPathsWithAssumedReadAccess.end();
673 if (std::find_if(m_localPathsWithAssumedReadAccess.begin(), localPathsEnd, startsWithURLPath) != localPathsEnd)
674 return true;
675
676 return false;
677}
678
679bool WebProcessProxy::checkURLReceivedFromWebProcess(const String& urlString, CheckBackForwardList checkBackForwardList)
680{
681 return checkURLReceivedFromWebProcess(URL(URL(), urlString), checkBackForwardList);
682}
683
684bool WebProcessProxy::checkURLReceivedFromWebProcess(const URL& url, CheckBackForwardList checkBackForwardList)
685{
686 // FIXME: Consider checking that the URL is valid. Currently, WebProcess sends invalid URLs in many cases, but it probably doesn't have good reasons to do that.
687
688 // Any other non-file URL is OK.
689 if (!url.isLocalFile())
690 return true;
691
692 // Any file URL is also OK if we've loaded a file URL through API before, granting universal read access.
693 if (m_mayHaveUniversalFileReadSandboxExtension)
694 return true;
695
696 // If we loaded a string with a file base URL before, loading resources from that subdirectory is fine.
697 if (hasAssumedReadAccessToURL(url))
698 return true;
699
700 // Items in back/forward list have been already checked.
701 // One case where we don't have sandbox extensions for file URLs in b/f list is if the list has been reinstated after a crash or a browser restart.
702 if (checkBackForwardList == CheckBackForwardList::Yes) {
703 String path = url.fileSystemPath();
704 for (auto& item : WebBackForwardListItem::allItems().values()) {
705 URL itemURL(URL(), item->url());
706 if (itemURL.isLocalFile() && itemURL.fileSystemPath() == path)
707 return true;
708 URL itemOriginalURL(URL(), item->originalURL());
709 if (itemOriginalURL.isLocalFile() && itemOriginalURL.fileSystemPath() == path)
710 return true;
711 }
712 }
713
714 // A Web process that was never asked to load a file URL should not ever ask us to do anything with a file URL.
715 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(Loading, "checkURLReceivedFromWebProcess: Received an unexpected URL from the web process");
716 return false;
717}

731bool WebProcessProxy::hasProvisionalPageWithID(WebPageProxyIdentifier pageID) const
732{
733 for (auto* provisionalPage : m_provisionalPages) {
734 if (provisionalPage->page().identifier() == pageID)
735 return true;
736 }
737 return false;
738}
739
740bool WebProcessProxy::isAllowedToUpdateBackForwardItem(WebBackForwardListItem& item) const
741{
742 if (m_pageMap.contains(item.pageID()))
743 return true;
744
745 if (hasProvisionalPageWithID(item.pageID()))
746 return true;
747
748 if (item.suspendedPage() && item.suspendedPage()->page().identifier() == item.pageID() && &item.suspendedPage()->process() == this)
749 return true;
750
751 return false;
752}
753
754void WebProcessProxy::updateBackForwardItem(const BackForwardListItemState& itemState)
755{
756 auto* item = WebBackForwardListItem::itemForID(itemState.identifier);
757 if (!item || !isAllowedToUpdateBackForwardItem(*item))
758 return;
759
760 item->setPageState(PageState { itemState.pageState });
761
762 if (!!item->backForwardCacheEntry() != itemState.hasCachedPage) {
763 if (itemState.hasCachedPage)
764 processPool().backForwardCache().addEntry(*item, coreProcessIdentifier());
765 else if (!item->suspendedPage())
766 processPool().backForwardCache().removeEntry(*item);
767 }
768}

771void WebProcessProxy::getPlugins(bool refresh, CompletionHandler<void(Vector<PluginInfo>&& plugins, Vector<PluginInfo>&& applicationPlugins, std::optional<Vector<WebCore::SupportedPluginIdentifier>>&& supportedPluginIdentifiers)>&& completionHandler)
772{
773 if (refresh)
774 m_processPool->pluginInfoStore().refresh();
775

777

784#if ENABLE(PDFKIT_PLUGIN)

786 if (!m_processPool->omitPDFSupport()) {
787 plugins.append(PDFPlugin::pluginInfo());
788 applicationPlugins.append(PDFPlugin::pluginInfo());
789 }
790#endif
791 completionHandler(WTFMove(plugins), WTFMove(applicationPlugins), WTFMove(supportedPluginIdentifiers));
792}
793#endif // ENABLE(NETSCAPE_PLUGIN_API)

815void WebProcessProxy::gpuProcessExited(GPUProcessTerminationReason reason)

846void WebProcessProxy::didReceiveMessage(IPC::Connection& connection, IPC::Decoder& decoder)
847{
848 if (dispatchMessage(connection, decoder))
849 return;
850
851 if (m_processPool->dispatchMessage(connection, decoder))
852 return;
853
854 if (decoder.messageReceiverName() == Messages::WebProcessProxy::messageReceiverName()) {
855 didReceiveWebProcessProxyMessage(connection, decoder);
856 return;
857 }
858
859 // FIXME: Add unhandled message logging.
860}
861
862bool WebProcessProxy::didReceiveSyncMessage(IPC::Connection& connection, IPC::Decoder& decoder, UniqueRef<IPC::Encoder>& replyEncoder)
863{
864 if (dispatchSyncMessage(connection, decoder, replyEncoder))
865 return true;
866
867 if (m_processPool->dispatchSyncMessage(connection, decoder, replyEncoder))
868 return true;
869
870 if (decoder.messageReceiverName() == Messages::WebProcessProxy::messageReceiverName())
871 return didReceiveSyncWebProcessProxyMessage(connection, decoder, replyEncoder);
872
873 // FIXME: Add unhandled message logging.
874 return false;
875}
876
877void WebProcessProxy::didClose(IPC::Connection& connection)
878{
879#if OS(DARWIN)
880 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(Process, "didClose: (web process %d crash)", connection.remoteProcessID());
881#else
882 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(Process, "didClose (web process crash)");
883#endif
884
885 processDidTerminateOrFailedToLaunch(ProcessTerminationReason::Crash);
886}
887
888void WebProcessProxy::processDidTerminateOrFailedToLaunch(ProcessTerminationReason reason)
889{
890 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(Process, "processDidTerminateOrFailedToLaunch: reason=%u", static_cast<unsigned>(reason));
891
892 // Protect ourselves, as the call to shutDown() below may otherwise cause us
893 // to be deleted before we can finish our work.
894 auto protectedThis = makeRef(*this);
895
896#if PLATFORM(COCOA) && ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
897 m_userMediaCaptureManagerProxy->clear();
898#endif
899
900#if ENABLE(ATTACHMENT_ELEMENT)
901 m_hasIssuedAttachmentElementRelatedSandboxExtensions = false;
902#endif
903
904 if (auto* webConnection = this->webConnection())
905 webConnection->didClose();
906
907 auto pages = copyToVectorOf<RefPtr<WebPageProxy>>(m_pageMap.values());
908 auto provisionalPages = WTF::map(m_provisionalPages, [](auto* provisionalPage) { return makeWeakPtr(provisionalPage); });
909
910 auto isResponsiveCallbacks = std::exchange(m_isResponsiveCallbacks, { });
911 for (auto& callback : isResponsiveCallbacks)
912 callback(false);
913
914 if (isStandaloneServiceWorkerProcess())
915 processPool().serviceWorkerProcessCrashed(*this);
916
917 shutDown();
918
919#if ENABLE(PUBLIC_SUFFIX_LIST)
920 if (pages.size() == 1 && reason == ProcessTerminationReason::Crash) {
921 auto& page = *pages[0];
922 String domain = topPrivatelyControlledDomain(URL({ }, page.currentURL()).host().toString());
923 if (!domain.isEmpty())
924 page.logDiagnosticMessageWithEnhancedPrivacy(WebCore::DiagnosticLoggingKeys::domainCausingCrashKey(), domain, WebCore::ShouldSample::No);
925 }
926#endif
927
928#if ENABLE(ROUTING_ARBITRATION)
929 m_routingArbitrator->processDidTerminate();
930#endif
931
932 // There is a nested transaction in WebPageProxy::resetStateAfterProcessExited() that we don't want to commit before the client call below (dispatchProcessDidTerminate).
933 Vector<PageLoadState::Transaction> pageLoadStateTransactions;
934 for (auto& page : pages) {
935 pageLoadStateTransactions.append(page->pageLoadState().transaction());
936 page->resetStateAfterProcessTermination(reason);
937 }
938
939 for (auto& provisionalPage : provisionalPages) {
940 if (provisionalPage)
941 provisionalPage->processDidTerminate();
942 }
943
944 for (auto& page : pages)
945 page->dispatchProcessDidTerminate(reason);
946
947 m_sleepDisablers.clear();
948}
949
950void WebProcessProxy::didReceiveInvalidMessage(IPC::Connection& connection, IPC::MessageName messageName)
951{
952 logInvalidMessage(connection, messageName);
953
954 WebProcessPool::didReceiveInvalidMessage(messageName);
955
956#if ENABLE(IPC_TESTING_API)
957 if (connection.ignoreInvalidMessageForTesting())
958 return;
959#endif
960
961 // Terminate the WebContent process.
962 terminate();
963
964 // Since we've invalidated the connection we'll never get a IPC::Connection::Client::didClose
965 // callback so we'll explicitly call it here instead.
966 didClose(connection);
967}
968
969void WebProcessProxy::didBecomeUnresponsive()
970{
971 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(Process, "didBecomeUnresponsive:");
972
973 auto protectedThis = makeRef(*this);
974
975 m_isResponsive = NoOrMaybe::No;
976
977 auto isResponsiveCallbacks = WTFMove(m_isResponsiveCallbacks);
978
979 for (auto& page : copyToVectorOf<RefPtr<WebPageProxy>>(m_pageMap.values()))
980 page->processDidBecomeUnresponsive();
981
982 bool isWebProcessResponsive = false;
983 for (auto& callback : isResponsiveCallbacks)
984 callback(isWebProcessResponsive);
985
986 // If the web process becomes unresponsive and only runs service workers, kill it ourselves since there are no native clients to do it.
987 if (isRunningServiceWorkers() && m_pageMap.isEmpty()) {
988 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(PerformanceLogging, "didBecomeUnresponsive: Terminating service worker-only web process because it is unresponsive");
989 disableServiceWorkers();
990 terminate();
991 }
992}
993
994void WebProcessProxy::didBecomeResponsive()
995{
996 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(Process, "didBecomeResponsive:");
997 m_isResponsive = NoOrMaybe::Maybe;
998
999 for (auto& page : copyToVectorOf<RefPtr<WebPageProxy>>(m_pageMap.values()))
1000 page->processDidBecomeResponsive();
1001}
1002
1003void WebProcessProxy::willChangeIsResponsive()

1005 for (auto& page : copyToVectorOf<RefPtr<WebPageProxy>>(m_pageMap.values()))
1006 page->willChangeProcessIsResponsive();
1007}
1008
1009void WebProcessProxy::didChangeIsResponsive()
1010{
1011 for (auto& page : copyToVectorOf<RefPtr<WebPageProxy>>(m_pageMap.values()))
1012 page->didChangeProcessIsResponsive();
1013}

1024void WebProcessProxy::didFinishLaunching(ProcessLauncher* launcher, IPC::Connection::Identifier connectionIdentifier)
1025{
1026 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(Process, "didFinishLaunching:");
1027 RELEASE_ASSERT(isMainThreadOrCheckDisabled());
1028
1029 auto protectedThis = makeRef(*this);
1030 AuxiliaryProcessProxy::didFinishLaunching(launcher, connectionIdentifier);
1031
1032 if (!IPC::Connection::identifierIsValid(connectionIdentifier)) {
1033 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(Process, "didFinishLaunching: Invalid connection identifier (web process failed to launch)");
1034 processDidTerminateOrFailedToLaunch(ProcessTerminationReason::Crash);
1035 return;
1036 }
1037
1038#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
1039 if (m_websiteDataStore)
1040 m_websiteDataStore->sendNetworkProcessXPCEndpointToWebProcess(*this);
1041#endif
1042
1043 RELEASE_ASSERT(!m_webConnection);
1044 m_webConnection = WebConnectionToWebProcess::create(this);
1045
1046 m_processPool->processDidFinishLaunching(*this);
1047 m_backgroundResponsivenessTimer.updateState();
1048
1049#if ENABLE(IPC_TESTING_API)
1050 if (m_ignoreInvalidMessageForTesting)
1051 connection()->setIgnoreInvalidMessageForTesting();
1052#endif
1053
1054#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
1055 if (connection()) {
1056 if (xpc_connection_t xpcConnection = connection()->xpcConnection())
1057 m_throttler.didConnectToProcess(xpc_connection_get_pid(xpcConnection));
1058 }
1059#endif
1060
1061#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
1062 unblockAccessibilityServerIfNeeded();
1063#if ENABLE(REMOTE_INSPECTOR)
1064 enableRemoteInspectorIfNeeded();
1065#endif
1066#endif
1067}

1086
1087void WebProcessProxy::didDestroyFrame(FrameIdentifier frameID)
1088{
1089 // If the page is closed before it has had the chance to send the DidCreateMainFrame message
1090 // back to the UIProcess, then the frameDestroyed message will still be received because it
1091 // gets sent directly to the WebProcessProxy.
1092 ASSERT(WebFrameProxyMap::isValidKey(frameID));
1093#if ENABLE(WEB_AUTHN)
1094 if (auto* frame = webFrame(frameID)) {
1095 if (auto* page = frame->page())
1096 page->websiteDataStore().authenticatorManager().cancelRequest(page->webPageID(), frameID);
1097 }
1098#endif
1099 if (auto* automationSession = m_processPool->automationSession())
1100 automationSession->didDestroyFrame(frameID);
1101 m_frameMap.remove(frameID);
1102}

1104void WebProcessProxy::disconnectFramesFromPage(WebPageProxy* page)
1105{
1106 for (auto& frame : copyToVector(m_frameMap.values())) {
1107 if (frame->page() == page)
1108 frame->webProcessWillShutDown();
1109 }
1110}

1147bool WebProcessProxy::canBeAddedToWebProcessCache() const
1148{
1149 if (isRunningServiceWorkers()) {
1150 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(Process, "canBeAddedToWebProcessCache: Not adding to process cache because the process is running workers");
1151 return false;
1152 }
1153
1154 if (WebKit::isInspectorProcessPool(processPool()))
1155 return false;
1156
1157 return true;
1158}
1159
1160void WebProcessProxy::maybeShutDown()
1161{
1162 if (isDummyProcessProxy() && m_pageMap.isEmpty()) {
1163 ASSERT(state() == State::Terminated);
1164 m_processPool->disconnectProcess(*this);
1165 return;
1166 }
1167
1168 if (state() == State::Terminated || !canTerminateAuxiliaryProcess())
1169 return;
1170
1171 if (canBeAddedToWebProcessCache() && processPool().webProcessCache().addProcessIfPossible(*this))
1172 return;
1173
1174 shutDown();
1175}
1176
1177bool WebProcessProxy::canTerminateAuxiliaryProcess()
1178{
1179 if (!m_pageMap.isEmpty() || m_suspendedPageCount || !m_provisionalPages.isEmpty() || m_isInProcessCache || m_shutdownPreventingScopeCounter.value()) {
1180 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(Process, "canTerminateAuxiliaryProcess: returns false (pageCount=%u, provisionalPageCount=%u, m_suspendedPageCount=%u, m_isInProcessCache=%d, m_shutdownPreventingScopeCounter=%lu)", m_pageMap.size(), m_provisionalPages.size(), m_suspendedPageCount, m_isInProcessCache, m_shutdownPreventingScopeCounter.value());
1181 return false;
1182 }
1183
1184 if (isRunningServiceWorkers()) {
1185 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(Process, "canTerminateAuxiliaryProcess: returns false because process is running service workers");
1186 return false;
1187 }
1188
1189 if (!m_processPool->shouldTerminate(*this)) {
1190 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(Process, "canTerminateAuxiliaryProcess: returns false because process termination is disabled");
1191 return false;
1192 }
1193
1194 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(Process, "canTerminateAuxiliaryProcess: returns true");
1195 return true;
1196}
1197
1198void WebProcessProxy::shouldTerminate(CompletionHandler<void(bool)>&& completionHandler)
1199{
1200 bool shouldTerminate = canTerminateAuxiliaryProcess();
1201 if (shouldTerminate) {
1202 // We know that the web process is going to terminate so start shutting it down in the UI process.
1203 shutDown();
1204 }
1205 completionHandler(shouldTerminate);
1206}

1274void WebProcessProxy::deleteWebsiteDataForOrigins(PAL::SessionID sessionID, OptionSet<WebsiteDataType> dataTypes, const Vector<WebCore::SecurityOriginData>& origins, CompletionHandler<void()>&& completionHandler)
1275{
1276 ASSERT(canSendMessage());
1277 ASSERT_UNUSED(sessionID, sessionID == this->sessionID());
1278
1279 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(ProcessSuspension, "deleteWebsiteDataForOrigins: Taking a background assertion because the Web process is deleting Website data for several origins");
1280
1281 sendWithAsyncReply(Messages::WebProcess::DeleteWebsiteDataForOrigins(dataTypes, origins), [this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)] () mutable {
1282#if RELEASE_LOG_DISABLED
1283 UNUSED_PARAM(this);
1284#endif
1285 completionHandler();
1286 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(ProcessSuspension, "deleteWebsiteDataForOrigins: Releasing a background assertion because the Web process is done deleting Website data for several origins");
1287 });
1288}
1289
1290void WebProcessProxy::requestTermination(ProcessTerminationReason reason)
1291{
1292 if (state() == State::Terminated)
1293 return;
1294
1295 auto protectedThis = makeRef(*this);
1296 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(Process, "requestTermination: reason=%d", reason);
1297
1298 AuxiliaryProcessProxy::terminate();
1299
1300 processDidTerminateOrFailedToLaunch(reason);
1301}
1302
1303void WebProcessProxy::enableSuddenTermination()
1304{
1305 if (state() != State::Running)
1306 return;
1307
1308 ASSERT(m_numberOfTimesSuddenTerminationWasDisabled);
1309 WebCore::enableSuddenTermination();
1310 --m_numberOfTimesSuddenTerminationWasDisabled;
1311}
1312
1313void WebProcessProxy::disableSuddenTermination()
1314{
1315 if (state() != State::Running)
1316 return;
1317
1318 WebCore::disableSuddenTermination();
1319 ++m_numberOfTimesSuddenTerminationWasDisabled;
1320}
1321
1322RefPtr<API::Object> WebProcessProxy::transformHandlesToObjects(API::Object* object)
1323{
1324 struct Transformer final : UserData::Transformer {
1325 Transformer(WebProcessProxy& webProcessProxy)
1326 : m_webProcessProxy(webProcessProxy)
1327 {
1328 }
1329
1330 bool shouldTransformObject(const API::Object& object) const override
1331 {
1332 switch (object.type()) {
1333 case API::Object::Type::FrameHandle:
1334 return static_cast<const API::FrameHandle&>(object).isAutoconverting();
1335
1336 case API::Object::Type::PageHandle:
1337 return static_cast<const API::PageHandle&>(object).isAutoconverting();
1338
1339 case API::Object::Type::PageGroupHandle:
1340#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
1341 case API::Object::Type::ObjCObjectGraph:
1342#endif
1343 return true;
1344
1345 default:
1346 return false;
1347 }
1348 }
1349
1350 RefPtr<API::Object> transformObject(API::Object& object) const override
1351 {
1352 switch (object.type()) {
1353 case API::Object::Type::FrameHandle:
1354 ASSERT(static_cast<API::FrameHandle&>(object).isAutoconverting());
1355 return m_webProcessProxy.webFrame(static_cast<API::FrameHandle&>(object).frameID());
1356
1357 case API::Object::Type::PageGroupHandle:
1358 return WebPageGroup::get(static_cast<API::PageGroupHandle&>(object).webPageGroupData().pageGroupID);
1359
1360 case API::Object::Type::PageHandle:
1361 ASSERT(static_cast<API::PageHandle&>(object).isAutoconverting());
1362 return m_webProcessProxy.webPage(static_cast<API::PageHandle&>(object).pageProxyID());
1363
1364#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
1365 case API::Object::Type::ObjCObjectGraph:
1366 return m_webProcessProxy.transformHandlesToObjects(static_cast<ObjCObjectGraph&>(object));
1367#endif
1368 default:
1369 return &object;
1370 }
1371 }
1372
1373 WebProcessProxy& m_webProcessProxy;
1374 };
1375
1376 return UserData::transform(object, Transformer(*this));
1377}
1378
1379RefPtr<API::Object> WebProcessProxy::transformObjectsToHandles(API::Object* object)
1380{
1381 struct Transformer final : UserData::Transformer {
1382 bool shouldTransformObject(const API::Object& object) const override
1383 {
1384 switch (object.type()) {
1385 case API::Object::Type::Frame:
1386 case API::Object::Type::Page:
1387 case API::Object::Type::PageGroup:
1388#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
1389 case API::Object::Type::ObjCObjectGraph:
1390#endif
1391 return true;
1392
1393 default:
1394 return false;
1395 }
1396 }
1397
1398 RefPtr<API::Object> transformObject(API::Object& object) const override
1399 {
1400 switch (object.type()) {
1401 case API::Object::Type::Frame:
1402 return API::FrameHandle::createAutoconverting(static_cast<const WebFrameProxy&>(object).frameID());
1403
1404 case API::Object::Type::Page:
1405 return API::PageHandle::createAutoconverting(static_cast<const WebPageProxy&>(object).identifier(), static_cast<const WebPageProxy&>(object).webPageID());
1406
1407 case API::Object::Type::PageGroup:
1408 return API::PageGroupHandle::create(WebPageGroupData(static_cast<const WebPageGroup&>(object).data()));
1409
1410#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
1411 case API::Object::Type::ObjCObjectGraph:
1412 return transformObjectsToHandles(static_cast<ObjCObjectGraph&>(object));
1413#endif
1414
1415 default:
1416 return &object;
1417 }
1418 }
1419 };
1420
1421 return UserData::transform(object, Transformer());
1422}

1436
1437void WebProcessProxy::didSetAssertionType(ProcessAssertionType type)
1438{
1439 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(ProcessSuspension, "didSetAssertionType: type=%u", type);
1440
1441 if (isStandaloneServiceWorkerProcess()) {
1442 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(ProcessSuspension, "didSetAssertionType: Release all assertions for network process because this is a service worker process without page");
1443 m_foregroundToken = nullptr;
1444 m_backgroundToken = nullptr;
1445 return;
1446 }
1447
1448 ASSERT(!m_backgroundToken || !m_foregroundToken);
1449
1450 switch (type) {
1451 case ProcessAssertionType::Suspended:
1452 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(ProcessSuspension, "didSetAssertionType(Suspended) Release all assertions for network process");
1453 m_foregroundToken = nullptr;
1454 m_backgroundToken = nullptr;
1455#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
1456 for (auto& page : m_pageMap.values())
1457 page->processWillBecomeSuspended();
1458#endif
1459 break;
1460
1461 case ProcessAssertionType::Background:
1462 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(ProcessSuspension, "didSetAssertionType(Background) Taking background assertion for network process");
1463 m_backgroundToken = processPool().backgroundWebProcessToken();
1464 m_foregroundToken = nullptr;
1465 break;
1466
1467 case ProcessAssertionType::Foreground:
1468 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(ProcessSuspension, "didSetAssertionType(Foreground) Taking foreground assertion for network process");
1469 m_foregroundToken = processPool().foregroundWebProcessToken();
1470 m_backgroundToken = nullptr;
1471#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
1472 for (auto& page : m_pageMap.values())
1473 page->processWillBecomeForeground();
1474#endif
1475 break;
1476
1477 case ProcessAssertionType::MediaPlayback:
1478 case ProcessAssertionType::UnboundedNetworking:
1479 case ProcessAssertionType::FinishTaskUninterruptable:
1480 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1481 }
1482
1483 ASSERT(!m_backgroundToken || !m_foregroundToken);
1484}
1485
1486void WebProcessProxy::updateAudibleMediaAssertions()
1487{
1488 bool newHasAudibleWebPage = WTF::anyOf(m_pageMap.values(), [] (auto& page) { return page->isPlayingAudio(); });
1489
1490 bool hasAudibleMediaActivity = !!m_audibleMediaActivity;
1491 if (hasAudibleMediaActivity == newHasAudibleWebPage)
1492 return;
1493
1494 if (newHasAudibleWebPage) {
1495 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(ProcessSuspension, "updateAudibleMediaAssertions: Taking MediaPlayback assertion for WebProcess");
1496 m_audibleMediaActivity = AudibleMediaActivity {
1497 makeUniqueRef<ProcessAssertion>(processIdentifier(), "WebKit Media Playback"_s, ProcessAssertionType::MediaPlayback),
1498 processPool().webProcessWithAudibleMediaToken()
1499 };
1500 } else {
1501 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(ProcessSuspension, "updateAudibleMediaAssertions: Releasing MediaPlayback assertion for WebProcess");
1502 m_audibleMediaActivity = std::nullopt;
1503 }
1504}

1518
1519void WebProcessProxy::isResponsive(CompletionHandler<void(bool isWebProcessResponsive)>&& callback)
1520{
1521 if (m_isResponsive == NoOrMaybe::No) {
1522 if (callback) {
1523 RunLoop::main().dispatch([callback = WTFMove(callback)]() mutable {
1524 bool isWebProcessResponsive = false;
1525 callback(isWebProcessResponsive);
1526 });
1527 }
1528 return;
1529 }
1530
1531 if (callback)
1532 m_isResponsiveCallbacks.append(WTFMove(callback));
1533
1534 checkForResponsiveness([weakThis = makeWeakPtr(*this)]() mutable {
1535 if (!weakThis)
1536 return;
1537
1538 for (auto& isResponsive : std::exchange(weakThis->m_isResponsiveCallbacks, { }))
1539 isResponsive(true);
1540 });
1541}
1542
1543void WebProcessProxy::isResponsiveWithLazyStop()
1544{
1545 if (m_isResponsive == NoOrMaybe::No)
1546 return;
1547
1548 if (!responsivenessTimer().hasActiveTimer()) {
1549 // We do not send a ping if we are already waiting for the WebProcess.
1550 // Spamming pings on a slow web process is not helpful.
1551 checkForResponsiveness([weakThis = makeWeakPtr(*this)]() mutable {
1552 if (!weakThis)
1553 return;
1554
1555 for (auto& isResponsive : std::exchange(weakThis->m_isResponsiveCallbacks, { }))
1556 isResponsive(true);
1557 }, UseLazyStop::Yes);
1558 }
1559}

1607
1608void WebProcessProxy::didExceedCPULimit()
1609{
1610 auto protectedThis = makeRef(*this);
1611
1612 for (auto& page : pages()) {
1613 if (page->isPlayingAudio()) {
1614 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(PerformanceLogging, "didExceedCPULimit: WebProcess has exceeded the background CPU limit but we are not terminating it because there is audio playing");
1615 return;
1616 }
1617
1618 if (page->hasActiveAudioStream() || page->hasActiveVideoStream()) {
1619 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(PerformanceLogging, "didExceedCPULimit: WebProcess has exceeded the background CPU limit but we are not terminating it because it is capturing audio / video");
1620 return;
1621 }
1622 }
1623
1624 bool hasVisiblePage = false;
1625 for (auto& page : pages()) {
1626 if (page->isViewVisible()) {
1627 page->didExceedBackgroundCPULimitWhileInForeground();
1628 hasVisiblePage = true;
1629 }
1630 }
1631
1632 // We only notify the client that the process exceeded the CPU limit when it is visible, we do not terminate it.
1633 if (hasVisiblePage)
1634 return;
1635
1636 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(PerformanceLogging, "didExceedCPULimit: Terminating background WebProcess that has exceeded the background CPU limit");
1637 logDiagnosticMessageForResourceLimitTermination(DiagnosticLoggingKeys::exceededBackgroundCPULimitKey());
1638 requestTermination(ProcessTerminationReason::ExceededCPULimit);
1639}

1644}

1665void WebProcessProxy::didStartProvisionalLoadForMainFrame(const URL& url)
1666{
1667 RELEASE_ASSERT(!isInProcessCache());
1668 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(Loading, "didStartProvisionalLoadForMainFrame:");
1669
1670 // This process has been used for several registrable domains already.
1671 if (m_registrableDomain && m_registrableDomain->isEmpty())
1672 return;
1673
1674 if (url.protocolIsAbout())
1675 return;
1676
1677 if (!url.protocolIsInHTTPFamily() && !processPool().configuration().processSwapsOnNavigationWithinSameNonHTTPFamilyProtocol()) {
1678 // Unless the processSwapsOnNavigationWithinSameNonHTTPFamilyProtocol flag is set, we don't process swap on navigations withing the same
1679 // non HTTP(s) protocol. For this reason, we ignore the registrable domain and processes are not eligible for the process cache.
1680 m_registrableDomain = WebCore::RegistrableDomain { };
1681 return;
1682 }
1683
1684 auto registrableDomain = WebCore::RegistrableDomain { url };
1685 if (m_registrableDomain && *m_registrableDomain != registrableDomain) {
1686#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
1687 disableServiceWorkers();
1688#endif
1689 // Null out registrable domain since this process has now been used for several domains.
1690 m_registrableDomain = WebCore::RegistrableDomain { };
1691 return;
1692 }
1693
1694 // Associate the process with this registrable domain.
1695 m_registrableDomain = WTFMove(registrableDomain);
1696}

1711 if (!m_suspendedPageCount) {

1713 maybeShutDown();
1714 }

1738void WebProcessProxy::createSpeechRecognitionServer(SpeechRecognitionServerIdentifier identifier)
1739{
1740 WebPageProxy* targetPage = nullptr;
1741 for (auto* page : pages()) {
1742 if (page && page->webPageID() == identifier) {
1743 targetPage = page;
1744 break;
1745 }
1746 }
1747
1748 if (!targetPage)
1749 return;
1750
1751 ASSERT(!m_speechRecognitionServerMap.contains(identifier));
1752 MESSAGE_CHECK(!m_speechRecognitionServerMap.contains(identifier));
1753
1754 auto& speechRecognitionServer = m_speechRecognitionServerMap.add(identifier, nullptr).iterator->value;
1755 auto permissionChecker = [weakPage = makeWeakPtr(targetPage)](auto& request, auto&& completionHandler) mutable {
1756 if (!weakPage) {
1757 completionHandler(WebCore::SpeechRecognitionError { SpeechRecognitionErrorType::NotAllowed, "Page no longer exists"_s });
1758 return;
1759 }
1760
1761 weakPage->requestSpeechRecognitionPermission(request, WTFMove(completionHandler));
1762 };
1763 auto checkIfMockCaptureDevicesEnabled = [weakPage = makeWeakPtr(targetPage)]() {
1764 return weakPage && weakPage->preferences().mockCaptureDevicesEnabled();
1765 };
1766
1767#if ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
1768 auto createRealtimeMediaSource = [weakPage = makeWeakPtr(targetPage)]() {
1769 return weakPage ? weakPage->createRealtimeMediaSourceForSpeechRecognition() : CaptureSourceOrError { "Page is invalid" };
1770 };
1771 speechRecognitionServer = makeUnique<SpeechRecognitionServer>(makeRef(*connection()), identifier, WTFMove(permissionChecker), WTFMove(checkIfMockCaptureDevicesEnabled), WTFMove(createRealtimeMediaSource));
1772#else
1773 speechRecognitionServer = makeUnique<SpeechRecognitionServer>(makeRef(*connection()), identifier, WTFMove(permissionChecker), WTFMove(checkIfMockCaptureDevicesEnabled));
1774#endif
1775
1776 addMessageReceiver(Messages::SpeechRecognitionServer::messageReceiverName(), identifier, *speechRecognitionServer);
1777}
1778
1779void WebProcessProxy::destroySpeechRecognitionServer(SpeechRecognitionServerIdentifier identifier)
1780{
1781 if (auto server = m_speechRecognitionServerMap.take(identifier))
1782 removeMessageReceiver(Messages::SpeechRecognitionServer::messageReceiverName(), identifier);
1783}
1784
1785#if ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
1786
1787SpeechRecognitionRemoteRealtimeMediaSourceManager& WebProcessProxy::ensureSpeechRecognitionRemoteRealtimeMediaSourceManager()
1788{
1789 if (!m_speechRecognitionRemoteRealtimeMediaSourceManager) {
1790 m_speechRecognitionRemoteRealtimeMediaSourceManager = makeUnique<SpeechRecognitionRemoteRealtimeMediaSourceManager>(makeRef(*connection()));
1791 addMessageReceiver(Messages::SpeechRecognitionRemoteRealtimeMediaSourceManager::messageReceiverName(), *m_speechRecognitionRemoteRealtimeMediaSourceManager);
1792 }
1793
1794 return *m_speechRecognitionRemoteRealtimeMediaSourceManager;
1795}

1876
1877void WebProcessProxy::updateServiceWorkerProcessAssertion()
1878{
1879 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(ProcessSuspension, "updateServiceWorkerProcessAssertion:");
1880 ASSERT(m_serviceWorkerInformation);
1881 if (!m_serviceWorkerInformation)
1882 return;
1883
1884 bool shouldTakeForegroundActivity = WTF::anyOf(m_serviceWorkerInformation->clientProcesses, [&](auto& process) {
1885 return &process != this && !!process.m_foregroundToken;
1886 });
1887 if (shouldTakeForegroundActivity) {
1888 if (!ProcessThrottler::isValidForegroundActivity(m_serviceWorkerInformation->activity))
1889 m_serviceWorkerInformation->activity = m_throttler.foregroundActivity("Service Worker for foreground view(s)"_s);
1890 return;
1891 }
1892
1893 bool shouldTakeBackgroundActivity = WTF::anyOf(m_serviceWorkerInformation->clientProcesses, [&](auto& process) {
1894 return &process != this && !!process.m_backgroundToken;
1895 });
1896 if (shouldTakeBackgroundActivity) {
1897 if (!ProcessThrottler::isValidBackgroundActivity(m_serviceWorkerInformation->activity))
1898 m_serviceWorkerInformation->activity = m_throttler.backgroundActivity("Service Worker for background view(s)"_s);
1899 return;
1900 }
1901 m_serviceWorkerInformation->activity = nullptr;
1902}
1903
1904void WebProcessProxy::registerServiceWorkerClientProcess(WebProcessProxy& proxy)
1905{
1906 if (!m_serviceWorkerInformation)
1907 return;
1908
1909 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(ServiceWorker, "registerServiceWorkerClientProcess: clientProcess=%p, clientPID=%d", &proxy, proxy.processIdentifier());
1910 m_serviceWorkerInformation->clientProcesses.add(proxy);
1911 updateServiceWorkerProcessAssertion();
1912}
1913
1914void WebProcessProxy::unregisterServiceWorkerClientProcess(WebProcessProxy& proxy)
1915{
1916 if (!m_serviceWorkerInformation)
1917 return;
1918
1919 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(ServiceWorker, "unregisterServiceWorkerClientProcess: clientProcess=%p, clientPID=%d", &proxy, proxy.processIdentifier());
1920 m_serviceWorkerInformation->clientProcesses.remove(proxy);
1921 updateServiceWorkerProcessAssertion();
1922}

1925{
1926 return m_serviceWorkerInformation ? ProcessThrottler::isValidForegroundActivity(m_serviceWorkerInformation->activity) : false;
1927}

1929bool WebProcessProxy::hasServiceWorkerBackgroundActivityForTesting() const
1930{
1931 return m_serviceWorkerInformation ? ProcessThrottler::isValidBackgroundActivity(m_serviceWorkerInformation->activity) : false;
1932}

1934
1935void WebProcessProxy::disableServiceWorkers()
1936{
1937 if (!m_serviceWorkerInformation)
1938 return;
1939
1940 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(ServiceWorker, "disableServiceWorkers:");
1941 m_serviceWorkerInformation = { };
1942 updateBackgroundResponsivenessTimer();
1943
1944#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
1945 processPool().removeFromServiceWorkerProcesses(*this);
1946 send(Messages::WebSWContextManagerConnection::Close { }, 0);
1947#endif
1948
1949 maybeShutDown();
1950}

1952#if ENABLE(CONTENT_EXTENSIONS)
1953static Vector<std::pair<String, WebCompiledContentRuleListData>> contentRuleListsFromIdentifier(const std::optional<UserContentControllerIdentifier>& userContentControllerIdentifier)
1954{
1955 if (!userContentControllerIdentifier) {
1956 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1957 return { };
1958 }
1959
1960 auto* userContentController = WebUserContentControllerProxy::get(*userContentControllerIdentifier);
1961 if (!userContentController)
1962 return { };
1963
1964 return userContentController->contentRuleListData();
1965}
1966#endif
1967
1968void WebProcessProxy::enableServiceWorkers(const UserContentControllerIdentifier& userContentControllerIdentifier)
1969{
1970 ASSERT(m_registrableDomain && !m_registrableDomain->isEmpty());
1971 ASSERT(!m_serviceWorkerInformation);
1972 WEBPROCESSPROXY_RELEASE_LOG(ServiceWorker, "enableServiceWorkers:");
1973 m_serviceWorkerInformation = ServiceWorkerInformation {
1974 WebPageProxyIdentifier::generate(),
1975 PageIdentifier::generate(),
1976 ServiceWorkerInitializationData {
1977 userContentControllerIdentifier,
1978#if ENABLE(CONTENT_EXTENSIONS)
1979 contentRuleListsFromIdentifier(userContentControllerIdentifier),
1980#endif
1981 },
1982 nullptr,
1983 { }
1984 };
1985 updateBackgroundResponsivenessTimer();
1986#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
1987 updateServiceWorkerProcessAssertion();
1988#endif
1989}

1991void WebProcessProxy::didCreateSleepDisabler(SleepDisablerIdentifier identifier, const String& reason, bool display)
1992{
1993 MESSAGE_CHECK(!reason.isNull());
1994 auto sleepDisabler = makeUnique<WebCore::SleepDisabler>(reason.utf8().data(), display ? PAL::SleepDisabler::Type::Display : PAL::SleepDisabler::Type::System);
1995 m_sleepDisablers.add(identifier, WTFMove(sleepDisabler));
1996}
1997
1998void WebProcessProxy::didDestroySleepDisabler(SleepDisablerIdentifier identifier)
1999{
2000 m_sleepDisablers.remove(identifier);
2001}
2002
2003bool WebProcessProxy::hasSleepDisabler() const
2004{
2005 return !m_sleepDisablers.isEmpty();
2006}
